pullRequest.bodyText:
Functions API with BSON encoding/decoding:
Adds RealmFunctions with support for calling Stitch functions (legacy api) synchronously and asynchronously and with default or explicit codec registry for encoding and decoding objects.
public <T> T callFunction(String name, List<?> args, Class<T> resultClass)
public <T> T callFunction(String name, List<?> args, Class<T> resultClass, CodecRegistry codecRegistry)
public <T> RealmAsyncTask callFunctionAsync(String name, List<?> args, Class<T> resultClass, RealmApp.Callback<T> callback)
public <T> RealmAsyncTask callFunctionAsync(String name, List<?> args, Class<T> resultClass, CodecRegistry codecRegistry, RealmApp.Callback<T> callback)

The RealmFunctions instance is retrieved from RealmUser with default or explicit codec registry through:
public RealmFunctions getFunctions() 
public RealmFunctions getFunctions(CodecRegistry codecRegistry)

Arguments are encoded with the

 Argument/result encoding/decoding support. Defaults to codec registry for primitive types, BsonValues, and List and Map types
 Backend support
 Tests
 Test of invoking function only authorized to specific user
 Adobt final package/naming scheme
 Align async API across other MongoDB related APIs
 Ignored test due to C++ Parser issues

Closes #6807

